@startuml Secuencia — Emitir receta controlada

title Secuencia — Emitir receta controlada (incluye registro blockchain)

actor Medico
participant "Angular\n(web)" as Web
participant "Supabase Auth" as Supabase
participant "ms-gestion\nRecetaController" as Ctrl
participant "RecetaService" as Svc
database "PostgreSQL\nclinica_gestion" as DB
participant "BlockchainClient" as BC
participant "ms-blockchain\n/recetas" as MSBC
participant "Polygon Amoy\nRegistroRecetas.sol" as Polygon

Medico -> Web : Llena formulario y emite
Web -> Supabase : getSession() -> access_token
Web -> Ctrl : mutation emitirReceta(input)\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt>

Ctrl -> Ctrl : @PreAuthorize(hasRole('MEDICO'))\nUsuarioContext.current()
Ctrl -> Svc : emitir(safeInput)

Svc -> DB : SELECT paciente, medicamentos
Svc -> Svc : detectarControlado()
Svc -> DB : INSERT Receta + Detalles (estado=EMITIDA)

alt receta tiene medicamento controlado
  Svc -> Svc : canonicalize() -> sha256
  Svc -> BC : registrarReceta(canonico, pacienteId, medicoUid)
  BC -> MSBC : POST /recetas { documentoTexto, pacienteId, medicoUid }\nBearer <jwt>
  MSBC -> MSBC : verifica JWT (JWKS)
  MSBC -> Polygon : contract.registrar(hash, pacienteB32, medicoB32)
  Polygon --> MSBC : tx + RecetaRegistrada(id, ...)
  MSBC --> BC : { id, txHash, blockNumber, hash }
  BC --> Svc : RegistroBlockchain
  Svc -> DB : UPDATE receta SET hash, blockchain_tx, blockchain_id
end

Svc --> Ctrl : Receta persistida
Ctrl --> Web : { id, blockchainTx, estado, ... }
Web --> Medico : Muestra confirmacion + link Polygonscan

note over Svc, BC
Si la llamada a ms-blockchain falla (timeout/5xx),
la receta queda sin txHash y un @Scheduled
reintenta cada 60s.
end note

@enduml
